Definition

Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) combines an LLM with an external knowledge source. Before generating a response, the system retrieves relevant documents and includes them in the prompt to improve accuracy.

Real-world Analogy

Instead of answering an exam question from memory, you first open the textbook, find the correct information, and then write the answer.

Salesforce Example

A Salesforce AI Agent retrieves the latest company documentation, Apex classes, or Knowledge Articles before answering questions about a Salesforce Org.

Interview Question

Q: If LLMs are already trained on massive datasets, why is Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) still necessary?